			</div>

			<div class="two-third m-bottom-40">
				<p>
				Mobile advertising is more efficient and effective with our mobile ad management platform for agencies and marketers. Data-driven insights and streamlined operations help to improve campaign results across mobile display, search and rich
				media channels. At the foundation of our platform is DOJO, a mobile ad management and ad serving solution that
				helps agencies and marketers manage the entire scope of their mobile advertising
				programs. <br><br> DOJO includes all the necessary tools you need to execute mobile rich media or static mobile advertising campaigns on the devices you want to target. <a href="https://drive.google.com/a/phluant.com/file/d/0ByQaQrqwt8DcTmxoVjNGQURRazQ/view?usp=sharing">Learn more...</a>
				<BR><BR>
				</p>
			</div>

			<div class="clear"></div>

			<div class="list_carousel">
				<ul id="news-slides">
					<li>
						<div class="one-third m-bottom-45">
							<h3 class="m-bottom-25">Account Management</h3>
							<p>
								Create a domain structure that works for your organization. Configure multiple accounts with agency, brand, and campaign-level permissions. Dashboard views provide information on active campaign performance to provide easy oversight.
								<!-- <a class="read-more" id="news-1" href="popup/news_1.html"></a> -->
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="one-third m-bottom-45">
							<h3 class="m-bottom-25">Campaign Management</h3>
							<p>
								Configurable templates and lists help you to quickly build and manage new campaigns. Optimize and control budget with impression caps, as well as with device and geographic targeting.  Identify sites certified to run Phluant rich media ad formats, and submit new sites for Phluant certification before upcoming campaigns.
								<!-- <a class="read-more" id="news-2" href="popup/news_2.html"></a> -->
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="one-third m-bottom-45 last">
							<h3 class="m-bottom-25">Placement Management</h3>
							<p>
								Configure different parameters for each site, ad type, or device. Parameters include scheduling, rotation, sequencing, and weighting. These advanced features enable you to ensure accurate day parting, avoid creative burnout, and fine-tune messaging.
								<!-- <a class="read-more" id="news-2" href="popup/news_2.html"></a>	-->
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="one-third m-bottom-45">
							<h3 class="m-bottom-25">Conversion Tracking</h3>
							<p>
								Post-click conversions can help you measure a campaign's resonance and effectiveness even after it stops running. Phluant can tell you how many visitors saw an ad impression, yet did not click an ad, but later visited the site. Conversion tracking can help advertisers and provide more insight into click-through activities, campaign effectiveness, and site and placement efficacy.
								<!-- <a class="read-more" id="news-3" href="popup/news_3.html"></a>	-->
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="one-third m-bottom-45">
							<h3 class="m-bottom-25">Ad Trafficking</h3>
							<p>
								An easy-to-use web-based tool enables you to tackle the most complex media plans.  Quickly generate ad tags for an unlimited number of sites, mobile devices, placements, or creative campaigns. The import feature enables ad traffickers to upload detailed media plans via CSV.
								<!-- <a class="read-more" id="news-4" href="popup/news_4.html"></a>	-->
							</p>
						</div>
						<div class="one-third last">
							<h3 class="m-bottom-25">Mobile Analytics</h3>
							<p>
								Gain visibility into campaign performance across all devices, ad networks and publishers. Detailed analytics reports show performance at the carrier, location, device, channel, and user levels. An easy-to-use web-based interface makes it easy to review real-time performance by geography, time ranges, date ranges, device, operating system or carrier, and drill down through reports at the advertiser, campaign, site, ad and creative levels to provide insight into which ads performed best on which sites.
								<!-- <a class="read-more" id="news-5" href="popup/news_5.html"></a>	-->
							</p>
						</div>

					</li>

				</ul>
