									<li>Separate PSD for each ad unit with animated assets in separate clearly defined layers</li>
								</ul>
								<p>Synched animated tablet ads work in tandem on the same screen to tell a bigger story. Animation starts in one banner ad and then continues in another ad unit elsewhere on the screen without missing a beat. The Tag Team format works only on tablets, and requires a minimum of two known above-the- fold placements on the same page. Publishers that offer the Tag Team synched ad unit includes:</p>
								<p>• Accuweather • eHow  • The Demand Network • NBC Universal</p>
								<h4>Benefits</h4>
								<ul>
									<li>Two above-the-fold units capture larger Share of Voice</li>
									<li>Unique format grabs the audience's attention</li>
									<li>Provides two canvases to showcase complex animation and tell bigger narrative</li>
								</ul>
								<a href="download/PS_TagTeam.pdf">Download the PDF (0.8MB)</a>
								<p class="readmore-close"><span></span>close</p>
							</div><!-- end .readmore-section -->
							<p class="readmore"><span></span>read more</p>
						</div>

					</li>

				</ul>
			</div>
		</div>
		<div class="features container clearfix">
			<div class="header one-half clearfix"><div class="summary-small-dark-bg"><span> mobile ad features </span></div></div>
			<div class="clear"></div>
			<div class="clearfix"><p>Powerful ad features build meaningful consumer engagement.</p></div>

			<div class="one-third">
				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image1" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('autoexpand','image1');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('autoexpand','image1');">Auto Expand</span>
					<div id="autoexpand" class="hiddenRow">
						Deliver quick, high-impact “sneak peeks” of the ad to users when they arrive on a web page. Upon initial page load, pre-expandable ads slides open, exposing the user to a larger rich media ad space. After a pre-set amount of time (5-7 seconds), the ad automatically snaps back to its original, standard ad unit size. The user can tap or click the banner to expose the panel and interact with the various features and functionality. *may incur additional fee
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image2" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('data','image2');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('data','image2');">Data Collection</span>
					<div id="data" class="hiddenRow">
						Email acquisition, polls, and quizzes via Data Collection.
						Data Collection feature can be used in any rich media ad format to facilitate polls, quizzes, and contests; or used to collect email or SMS opt-ins and other forms of data collection.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image3" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('gallery','image3');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('gallery','image3');">Gallery/Carousel</span>
					<div id="gallery" class="hiddenRow">
						Galleries are an easy way to showcase product images and features. Ideal for any industry, including auto manufacturers, retailers, travel, and fashion, image galleries can be incorporated into any rich media ad format to improve navigation of several panels worth of mobile content. Images can scroll up, down, left, or right or infinite loop or auto-rotate per client specification.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image4" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('location','image4');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('location','image4');">Store Locator</span>
					<div id="location" class="hiddenRow">
						Store locators show users the advertiser’s nearest location to drive foot traffic. Ideal for auto manufacturers, hotels, quick-service restaurants, retailers, and consumer products, the Store Locator feature uses a device’s built-in GPS to present the nearest locations in Google, Mapquest or Bing Maps and provide directions. This feature can be used in a banner ad or within the expand panel.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image5" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('distance','image5');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('distance','image5');">Distance Locator</span>
					<div id="distance" class="hiddenRow">
						Drive traffic to brick and mortar establishments by showing the distance to the nearest retailer or service location.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="one-third">
				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image6" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('calendar','image6');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('calendar','image6');">Add-to-Calendar</span>
					<div id="calendar" class="hiddenRow">
						Make your mobile campaign unforgettable with the Add-to-Calendar feature. Ideal for entertainment, retail, and performance advertisers, Add-to-Calendar enables users to add your big event to their native device calendar, or remind themselves to follow up on your special offer by creating a special reminder.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image7" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('sequencing','image7');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('sequencing','image7');">Session-Based Sequencing</span>
					<div id="sequencing" class="hiddenRow">
						Create a longer narrative with multiple ad units. Multiple messages can be shown within a banner ad to increase exposure to a brand’s full campaign story. Advertisers can decide which message to serve to a user depending on previous interaction or ads seen. Sequencing can be paired with session-based frequency capping to create a sophisticated mobile campaign that takes the user down a purchase path.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image8" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('frequency','image8');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('frequency','image8');">Session-Based Frequency Capping</span>
					<div id="frequency" class="hiddenRow">
						Limit the number of times a user is exposed to the same creative. Session-based frequency capping enables agencies to build multiple creative ad units and control how often a user sees each unit during a single browser or app session. This option can help maximize media plans and control costs by limiting the premium ad formats shown to a single user to one impression, and show less-expensive units for subsequent impressions.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image9" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('rotation','image9');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('rotation','image9');">Session-Based Rotation</span>
					<div id="rotation" class="hiddenRow">
						Avoid creative burnout by rotating different creative ads within the same browser or app session.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image10" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('ISI','image10');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('ISI','image10');">ISI/Disclaimer</span>
					<div id="ISI" class="hiddenRow">
					Legal disclaimers or Important Safety Information (ISI) can be displayed in either a separate window or embedded within the banner ad. ISI options include: auto-expand (partial or full-screen) and auto-collapse, auto-scrolling, or expand upon user's click.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="one-third">
				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image11" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('hotspot','image11');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('hotspot','image11');">Hotspot</span>
					<div id="hotspot" class="hiddenRow">
						Touch-activated hotspots can be used to highlight product features or provide interactive messaging throughout any rich media ad format. When a user taps on a hotspot, the icon will expand into a content or image area, allowing the user to view and scroll content, then tap again to close and move on to another area. Hotspots increase the amount of time a user engages with your ad and your overall interaction rate.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image12" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('Accelerometer','image12');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('Accelerometer','image12');">Accelerometer</span>
					<div id="Accelerometer" class="hiddenRow">
						Utilize a device’s accelerometer within any rich media ad format by tilting, turning, or shaking the device to launch animation, change images, or launch a video. Giving consumers a way to interact with the ad increases engagement and reinforces your brand messaging.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image13" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('in-line','image13');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('in-line','image13');">In-line Banner Video</span>
					<div id="in-line" class="hiddenRow">
						In-line video auto-plays short video clips within any rich media ad format to capture the eye and encourage consumer engagement. Teaser videos can be expanded to feature longer videos or other ad features.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image14" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('erase','image14');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('erase','image14');">Swipe–to-Erase</span>
					<div id="erase" class="hiddenRow">
						Swipe is a touchscreen gesture that is guaranteed to entice users to engage with your ads. Advertisers can use Swipe in many different ways including Swipe-to-Rotate, which allows users to see a full view of products. Swipe-to-Change lets consumers swipe across the screen to change or alter an image or character, while Swipe-to-Erase gets users to rub the screen to erase or “scratch off” to reveal a new image.
					</div>
				</div>

				<div class="visibleFeature">
					<img id="image15" border="0" src="images/expand.png" onClick="showHide('games','image15');">&nbsp;
					<span onClick="showHide('games','image15');">Games</span>
					<div id="games" class="hiddenRow">
						You design it, we build it.
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</div>

